== Basmati Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it comes to the boil, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Chicken Saag Curry ==

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @pasanda style seasoning{1%sachet}.

Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack}, @water for the curry{150%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @creme fraiche{75%g} to the frying pan. Stir to combine.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat.

Simmer until the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Finishing ==

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the @mango chutney{40%g} through the curry.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted.

Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.

== Serving ==

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the chicken saag curry.

Top with the @crispy onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!